# PowerShell Script to List Common MMC Consoles
# This script generates a table of common Microsoft Management Console (MMC) consoles
# along with their filenames, purposes, and usage shortcuts.



| **MMC Console**                        | **Filename (.msc)**   | **Purpose**                                       | **Usage / Shortcut**              |
| -------------------------------------- | --------------------- | ------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------- |
| **Device Manager**                     | `devmgmt.msc`         | Manage hardware devices and drivers               | `Win + R` → `devmgmt.msc`         |
| **Services**                           | `services.msc`        | Manage Windows services (start/stop/configure)    | `Win + R` → `services.msc`        |
| **Event Viewer**                       | `eventvwr.msc`        | View system, security, and application logs       | `Win + R` → `eventvwr.msc`        |
| **Local Group Policy Editor**          | `gpedit.msc`          | Configure local Group Policy settings             | `Win + R` → `gpedit.msc`          |
| **Computer Management**                | `compmgmt.msc`        | Central management: disk, devices, event logs     | `Win + R` → `compmgmt.msc`        |
| **Disk Management**                    | `diskmgmt.msc`        | Manage partitions and volumes                     | `Win + R` → `diskmgmt.msc`        |
| **Task Scheduler**                     | `taskschd.msc`        | Automate and manage scheduled tasks               | `Win + R` → `taskschd.msc`        |
| **Performance Monitor**                | `perfmon.msc`         | Monitor and analyze system performance            | `Win + R` → `perfmon.msc`         |
| **Windows Firewall Advanced**          | `wf.msc`              | Configure advanced firewall and security policies | `Win + R` → `wf.msc`              |
| **Active Directory Users & Computers** | `dsa.msc`             | Manage AD users, groups, computers (domain only)  | `Win + R` → `dsa.msc`             |
| **Group Policy Management Console**    | `gpmc.msc`            | Manage GPOs in Active Directory                   | `Win + R` → `gpmc.msc`            |
| **Print Management**                   | `printmanagement.msc` | Manage printers and print servers                 | `Win + R` → `printmanagement.msc` |
| **Local Security Policy**              | `secpol.msc`          | Configure local security settings                 | `Win + R` → `secpol.msc`          |
| **Component Services**                 | `comexp.msc`          | Manage COM+ applications and services             | `Win + R` → `comexp.msc`          |
| **Shared Folders**                     | `fsmgmt.msc`          | Manage shared folders and sessions                | `Win + R` → `fsmgmt.msc`          |
.msc